• About Algorave: Algorave is a live coding–based electronic music movement where sound is written and performed in real time. It was founded by Alex McLean and Nick Collins in the UK in 2011. Performances combine self-written code, music, and visuals projected live for the audience. (Algorave.com)<br/>
<br/>
• Algorave Music Practice in Indonesia: Paguyuban Algorave - Patrick Hartono &amp; Stevie J. Sutanto. Published by Cambridge University Press Online, 18 August 2023.<br/>
<br/>
𝗙𝗼𝗼𝘁𝗮𝗴𝗲:<br/>
<br/>
• Footage 1: Wasawat Somno (TH) - Algorapture Show, 10 October, Krapela, Jakarta.<br/>
<br/>
• Footage 2: 1st Paguyuban Algorave Indonesia Concert, 22 April 2021. Featuring: Patrick Hartono (SuperCollider), Tomy Herseta (Sonic Pi), Rangga Purnama Aji (TidalCycles).<br/>
<br/>
• Footage 3: Agustusan Paguyuban Algorave Indonesia Concert, 21 August 2022. Featuring: Rangga Purnama Aji.<br/>
<br/>
• Footage 4: 1st ALGORAPTURE - Live Coding Audio/Visual Surge, 10 October 2024, Krapela, Jakarta. Featuring: Wasawat Somno (TH), Steadystate (ID).<br/>
<br/>
• Footage 5: 3rd Algorapture - SEAquence Protocol, 3 August 2025, 97KoboLab. Featuring: andrawkx / RMPGNG SLRMN (ID) × Palindroma (RU/TH).<br/>
<br/>
• Footage 6: Monthly Algorapture sessions at 97KoboLab, circa 2025. Featuring: vlusky (ID), KAE (ID), CRSRCRSRRR (TH).<br/>
<br/>
- Algorapture was founded in Jakarta by andrawkx &amp; Steadystate.<br/>
- Paguyuban Algorave Indonesia was initiated in Yogyakarta by Bagas Koro Saputra, Mohammad Ali Azca, Maria Maya Aristya, Muhammad Khoirur Roziqin, and Rangga Purnama Aji.<br/>
<br/>
